# Known Pathology Labs & PDF Quirks

## Kokilaben Dhirubhai Ambani Hospital, Mumbai
- Text-based PDFs (pdfplumber works).
- Uses `—` em-dashes, `|` pipes, `_ .` artifacts as separators.
- Appends `-H`/`-L` flags to values. May prefix with `=—o` before units.
- Test names: "TSH Ultrasensitive (TSH)", "Free Triiodothyronine (Free T3)", "ACTH - Adreno Corticotropic".

## Lal PathLabs, Pune
- Text-based PDFs. Clean formatting with 2+ space separation.
- Test names: "T3, Total", "T4, Total", "TSH", "CORTISOL, MORNING, SERUM", "ACTH, PLASMA".

## SRL Diagnostics
- Text-based PDFs. Test names often have no spaces ("HDLCHOLESTEROL", "TSH3RDGENERATION").
- Unit after ref range: `T3 61.54 60.0 - 181.0 ng/dL`.

## Aarogyamm Pathology, Pune
- Text-based. Standard formatting similar to Lal PathLabs.

## Dr. Nagar Pathology, Ujjain (Kalpavraksha)
- OCR required (scanned reports). Short format: `THYROID STIMULATING HORMONE (TSH): 3.84 ulU/ml.`
- Units are garbled OCR: `ulU/ml` → `µIU/mL`.
- Often only has the test result and ref range on separate lines.

## Sancheti Hospital, Pune
- Text-based. Uses soft-hyphen (`\u00AD`) in ref ranges instead of dash.

## Agarwal Diagnostics, Ujjain
- OCR required for older reports.
